%I A395989 #9 May 13 2026 12:12:19
%S A395989 1,1,2,6,16,24,37,26,10,1,1,1,2,1
%N A395989 Number of transmission-minimal connected quartic graphs on n vertices.
%C A395989 Here, transmission means the Wiener index, the sum of distances between all unordered pairs of vertices.
%C A395989 The terms a(6)-a(17) are the entries in the "# of graphs" row of Table 2 of Knor, Škrekovski, and Tepeh (2019).
%H A395989 M. Knor, R. Škrekovski and A. Tepeh, <a href="https://match.pmf.kg.ac.rs/electronic_versions/Match81/n1/match81n1_119-132.pdf">Chemical Graphs with the Minimum Value of Wiener Index</a>,  MATCH Commun. Math. Comput. Chem. 81 (2019), 119-132.
%H A395989 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/notebooks/GraphTheory/Transmission-MinimalRegularGraph.nb">Transmission-Minimal Regular Graph</a>.
%e A395989 a(5) = 1, since the complete graph K_5 is the unique transmission-minimal connected quartic graph on 5 vertices.
%e A395989 a(8) = 6, since there are 6 transmission-minimal connected quartic graphs on 8 vertices.
%Y A395989 Cf. A395986 (minimal transmission for cubic graphs).
%Y A395989 Cf. A395987 (number of transmission-minimal cubic graphs).
%Y A395989 Cf. A395988 (minimal transmission for quartic graphs).
%K A395989 nonn,more,new
%O A395989 5,3
%A A395989 _Eric W. Weisstein_, May 13 2026
